FBIS3-3052 "drchi051_m_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-051 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Feb 1994 Military Aircraft Maintenance Crews Use High Technology OW0803120894 Beijing Central Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1400 GMT 19 Feb 94 OW0803120894 Beijing Central Television Program One Network in Mandarin 1400 GMT 19 Feb 94 Language: Mandarin Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report over video from the "Night News" program] [Text] The Air Force's aircraft maintenance troops extensively apply new and high technology, thus markedly improving their aircraft maintenance and support ability. [video shows pan shot of the interior of a garage where soldiers are seen working on machinery, then cuts to show five technicians in white coats servicing some instruments] Using computer software and modern (?earthquake-sounding) technology, aircraft maintenance troops have developed simulated training and instructional systems complete with images, texts, and sounds. To train maintenance crews in simulated maintenance, assembly, disassembly, and debugging services, and to cultivate high-level aircraft maintenance personnel, they have established an aircraft maintenance management network whose scope ranges from various large Air Force units to divisions and regiments. This has effectively improved the accuracy and timeliness of equipment maintenance. [video shows close-up shots of a computer keyboard, a diagram on a computer screen, and a pantograph moving across a sheet of white paper, then cuts to show men in military uniforms welding parts together and technicians in white coats adjusting instruments]
